canonical:
  title: 邵台輔讓兵部尙書知三司事不允批答
  author: 朴浩
  language: lzh
  text: 省表具之卿毓性該明秉心端直早契先王之遇久凝內侍之功屬我紹承首於推載積古今之勤瘁洽中外之見聞須升騎省之班用擢貂冠之貴一昨加尊寶冊歸美璇宮亦多幹事之勞敢闕旌能之典尋以翔榮八座仍令帶秩三司忽覽瀝誠恭伸敍讓雖載嘉於謙柄實難寢於言綸勉膺優異之恩永贊大寧之化所讓宜不允兼斷來章
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 邵台輔讓兵部尙書知三司事不允批答
  author: 朴浩
  language: lzh
  text: 省表具之。卿毓性該明。秉心端直。早契先王之遇。久凝內侍之功。屬我紹承。首於推載。積古今之勤瘁。洽中外之見聞。須升騎省之班。用擢貂冠之貴。一昨加尊寶冊。歸美璇宮。亦多幹事之勞。敢闕旌能之典。尋以翔榮八座。仍令帶秩三司。忽覽瀝誠。恭伸敍讓。雖載嘉於謙柄。實難寢於言綸。勉膺優異之恩。永贊大寧之化。所讓宜不允。兼斷來章。
korean:
  title: 소태보양 병부상서 지삼사사 불윤 비답
  author: 박호
  language: kor
  text: 올린 표(表)를 보고서 모든 내용을 다 알았다. 경은 타고난 성품이 두루 밝고 마음가짐이 단정하고 곧다. 일찍이 선왕의 알아준 바가 되어 오래도록 가까이에서 모신 공로를 이루었다. 내가 왕위를 이어받을 때에도 추대하는 데 앞장을 섰다. 처음부터 끝까지 공로를 쌓아서, 안팎의 보고 들음에 흐뭇하였다. 모름지기 기성(騎省)의 반열에 승진되어야겠기에, 초관(貂冠)의 귀한 자리에 발탁시켰었다. 엊그제 보책(寶冊)에 존호를 더해서 선궁(璇宮 후비(后妃)의 궁)에 귀미(歸美)할 때에도 또한 그 일을 주선하느라 수고가 많았으니, 감히 재능을 표창하는 의절을 빠뜨리겠는가.조금 전에 팔좌(八座)의 영광을 날리고, 인하여 삼사(三司)의 품질(品秩)을 띠게 하였다. 그랬더니 올린 말을 본즉, 공손히 사양할 뜻을 서술하였다. 비록 겸손한 것은 가상스러우나, 실로 발표한 명령을 철회하기는 어려웁다. 그러니 힘써 특별한 은혜를 받아서, 태평의 정치를 길이 협찬하도록 하라. 사양한 바는 마땅히 윤허하지 않고, 겸하여 다시 글 올리는 것을 금하노라.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0320_020_0010&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Imperial Rescript Declining the Request of Minister Park Hao to Relinquish His Posts as Minister of War and Director of the Three Departments
  author: Park Hao
  language: eng
  text: I have received and considered the full contents of your memorial. Your nature is broad and luminous, your character steadfast and upright. You earned the favor of our former king in your youth, and through long service in close attendance, have accumulated merit beyond measure. When I ascended the throne, you were foremost among those who supported my succession. From beginning to end, you have built a record of devoted service, earning the respect and admiration of all, both near and far. It was fitting to advance you to the rank of the Palace Secretariat and to elevate you to the honored post of the highest nobility. When we recently added titles to the imperial consort's testament of honor, the ceremonies proceeded smoothly through your careful stewardship—how could I overlook recognizing such capability? I appointed you to the prominence of the Eight Ministries and granted you concurrent position among the Three Departments. Yet upon reviewing your recent petition, you humbly express your wish to decline these honors. Though your modesty is admirable, I find it impossible to revoke what has been publicly proclaimed. Therefore, I urge you to accept these extraordinary marks of favor and continue your service in promoting the great peace of our realm. Your request for resignation is hereby denied. Furthermore, submit no further petitions on this matter.
  footnotes:
    - The 'Eight Ministries' (八座) refers to the highest executive posts in the government structure of the time.
    - The 'Three Departments' (三司) were central administrative divisions handling finances and oversight.
    - This is an imperial rescript refusing a minister's resignation, written in the formal style of royal decline.
